Been sitting on this one for a while.. 

This is LOVELY 

choreographed by me 
danced by @janravnik & @sievetaylor 

A piece about the mental and emotional toll that often lies beneath the surface of the picture of perfection. 

I was asked to submit a piece. I had 5 hours to set the choreography, and it could not be performed by “ballroom” dancers. It was a new and exciting challenge for me. I did not get the job, but I was so filled with happiness and gratitude that these incredible people took the time to create this with me. This is raw footage.. different than anything I have created before.. but in lieu of mental health awareness month, I wanted to share 🫶🏼

Thank you @janravnik & @sievetaylor for your incredible talent, and efforts in making this piece possible! 🫶🏼 thank you @codyjaymorgan for helping capture this, and HUGE thank you to @mihrankstudios for always supporting me and providing such a special space to create. 🤟🏼 

#brittcherrychoreo #mentalhealthawareness

I am always so amazed at what taking a dance class can do for the soul.

 I am so lucky to have found the beautiful @natalyaz_official! Having a background in ballroom also she and I connected instantly!! I have always admired her work but it wasn’t until this class that I truly got to see her shine!  Her passion for education radiates as she blends and melds the essence of Latin into her heels class. And for me, i LOVED it. 

For this class, my focus was to be kind to myself, and dance as long as the beauties next to me! It’s been so long since I have danced regularly since diving into producing so any chance I get, is a special one. 

Thanks @natalyaz_official, I’ll be back 💟

Come dance with me 💃🏻

In each class we take the time to break down the basics, fundamentals & figures of Latin Ballroom styles like: 

CHA CHA 
SAMBA 
RUMBA 
PASO DOBLE 
JIVE 

Whether you are new to ballroom or have been doing it for years, this class is for you!! Previous dance experience is recommended, but not necessary! 

SHOES: please wear comfortable/flexible shoes! I would rather you wear flats and be connected to the floor than dancing in a stiletto

ATTIRE: dress to impress!! Confidence is EVERYTHING!! If you dress the part, in something that makes you feel sassy, you are 100% going to commit more, and have more fun! 

PSA: we typically learn an intermediate combo, and occasionally do partnering, partners are not required! But it’s always more fun to bring a friend!!! 

If you have ANY questions, don’t hesitate to ask to comment here!
